20/12/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The formations in Romania's ruling alliance -- the National Liberal Party and the Democratic Party (PD) -- opened formal negotiations on their possible merger Monday (19 December).
The start of talks, sought repeatedly by President Traian Basescu, followed ceremonies marking the coalition government's first year in office.
In other news, a Slovak ship, the Polana, sank in the Danube River between Bulgaria and Romania Tuesday, after joint attempts to extinguish a fire onboard.
It was carrying some 40 tonnes of fuel, raising environmental concerns.
(Nine o'clock, Rompres, bTV - 20/12/05)
